AHK Menu Object Model

MENU Reference

I. Objects/Interfaces
	MENU[class]       - Class object
	MENU              - Represents a menu.
	MENU._menuitems_  - Represents the menu items in the menu.
	MENU._item_       - Represents a single menu item. MENU._item_ is the base interface for accessing a menu item's properties and methods.

II. Properties
	name              - Returns the name of the menu or the menu item.
	                  - Appies to MENU (Read-only) , MENU._item_ (Read/write)
    handle            - Returns the handle/hMenu of the menu.
                      - Applies to MENU (Read-only)
    count             - Returns the number of items in the menu.
                      - Applies to MENU (Read-only)
    default           - If the target object is a MENU object, this property contains the MENU._item_ object representing the default(if any) menu item.
                        If the target object is of the MENU._item_ type, this property returns True(1) if the item is currently the default item, otherwise, False(0).
                      - Appies to MENU (Read/write) , MENU._item_ (Read/write)
    icon              - Gets or sets the menu item's icon (file) and icon number(if any).
                      - Applies to MENU._item_ (Read/write)
    target            - Gets or sets the menu item's target label or function.
                      - Applies to MENU._item_ (Read/write)
    check             - Gets or sets the menu item's "check state".
                      - Applies to MENU._item_ (Read/write)
    enable            - Gets or sets the menu item's "enable state".
                      - Applies to MENU._item_ (Read/write)
    pos               - Returns the menu item's index/position in the menu.
                      - Applies to MENU._item_ (Read/write)
    type              - Returns the menu item's type [Normal , Submenu , Separator].
                      - Applies to MENU._item_ (Read-only)
    id                - Returns the menu item identifier of the menu item.
                      - Applies to MENU._item_ (Read-only)
    menu              - Represents the menu from which the menu item belongs to. 
                      - Applies to MENU._item_ (Read-only)
    isMenu            - returns True(1) if the menu exists, otherwise, False(0).
                      - Applies to MENU (Read-only)
    item              - Represents the MENU._menuitems_ object containg a list of all menu items for this menu.
                      - Applies to MENU (Read-only)
    *ItemPosOrName    - Represents the menu item with the specified name or index/pos.
                      - Applies to MENU._menuitems_ (Read-only)
    thisItem          - Represents the most recently selected menu item.
                      - When accessing this property, target object must be the class object not a derived object from the class.
                      - Applies to MENU[class] (Read-only)
    thisMenu          - Represents the menu from which the most recently selected menu item belongs to.
                      - When accessing this property, target object must be the class object not a derived object from the class.
                      - Applies to MENU[class] (Read-only)

III. Methods (see Method Details below for args details, examples, etc.)
	add               - Appends a new item to the end of the menu.
	                  - Applies to MENU
	insert            - Inserts a new menu item at the specified position in a menu. If position is not specified, the item is appended to the end of the menu.
	                  - Applies to MENU
	delete            - Deletes a menu item. If no item is specified, all menu items will be removed.
	                  - Applies to MENU
	show              - Displays the menu.
	                  - Applies to MENU
	setIcon           - Sets the menu item's icon.
	                  - Applies to MENU , MENU._item_

